HEAD and 3.1.x. All workspaces contained all imported binary plugin projects,

I then exited my 3.2-dev workspace, and noticed it wouldn't restart either with
similar failure.

I tried to start it with command line option: -clean, made no difference.
I then found the SDK/configuration folder, and replaced it with original one
from SDK build archive; and then I was able to restart my 2 workspaces in parallel.

Seems to be thus an issue of configuration data corruption.

Created an attachment (id=28091)
Offending configuration folder

Comment from JohnA:

Pascal: Philippe got into a state today where Eclipse would no longer startup.
He started to get classloading exceptions (pasted below)... From the sound of
it, deleting the configuration directory allowed him to restart.  He uses
multiple workspaces on the same configuration, so I suspect there was some
corruption of shared metadata in the configuration folder.
